	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;A few things to note here. First of all Fungi Tunics are still pretty rare on alot of servers, and those that have them will want no less than 30kpp for one. Iksar regen BP are about 6kpp on Luclin, still expensive but much more obtainable. Dont even think that you are going to be able to roll on a fungi as a shaman if it drops. Iceworm fangs are probably the nicest piercer you can weild pre-Epic, but are hard to find despite being shaman only--they are 6kpp minimum. Not sure what you are talking about on JB gear--I assume you meant the arms, gloves and helm as these are the 3 most common pieces. The BP only drops from Trakanon and the Legs ( clickable AGI buff ) only drop from Venril Sathir, head mob of KC. Note that these items are never for sale, and if you are an ogre or troll shaman hunting in KC will make you KOS in the OT Outpost, so unless you never plan on going thru there again dont hunt KC. You mention cannibalize 5/torpor combo, but as far as i know there is no Can 5--unless you are talking about the AA skill. Also torpor is level 60, and I believe it slows and snares you while its in effect, which is going to put a major damper on meleeing--i may be wrong. Also JBB's are rare as well, and when they come up for sale you will be about 10-15kpp lighter in the bank if you can get one. Casting your best root on a mob that is actively dotted and has a pet on it is a major waste of mana as its going to be broken very quickly--id use the level 5 root spell. Nice post if a late as any shaman who has all of this gear will Im sure already have a good method of getting items/XP. <br><br>54 Ogre Battleshaman on Luclin server--Aggrok<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
